[Naming Conventions (Detailed Method & Locator Patterns) > Element Locator Naming (Element-Prefixed)]

**Always prefix locator names with the element type:**

```typescript
public get locator() {
  return {
    // Buttons
    buttonSubmit: this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }),
    buttonCancel: this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Cancel' }),

    // Text inputs
    textBoxEmail: this.page.getByLabel('Email'),
    textBoxPassword: this.page.getByLabel('Password'),

    // Links
    linkForgotPassword: this.page.getByRole('link', { name: 'Forgot Password' }),

    // Dropdowns
    dropDownCountry: this.page.getByLabel('Country'),

    // Checkboxes
    checkBoxRememberMe: this.page.getByRole('checkbox', { name: 'Remember Me' }),
  };
}
```

[Naming Conventions (Detailed Method & Locator Patterns) > Environment-Agnostic Design]

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Uses descriptive names, works across environments
const legendItem = 'Awaiting Development';
await columnBar.assertLegendItemEnabled(legendItem);
await columnBar.toggleLegendItem(legendItem);
await columnBar.assertLegendItemDisabled(legendItem);

// ❌ BAD - Uses indices, breaks if order changes
