[Playwright Locator Hierarchy > Priority Order > 1. `getByRole()` / `getByTestId()` — CO-FIRST PRIORITY]

Use either as the first choice. Both are equally preferred in this project.

**`getByRole()` — for interactive elements**

```typescript
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign In' }).click();
await page.getByRole('textbox', { name: 'Email' }).fill('user@example.com');
await page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Welcome' });
```

✅ Reflects how users and assistive technologies perceive the page
✅ Surfaces accessibility issues early

**`getByTestId()` — for elements with `data-drid` attributes**

```typescript
// Uses data-drid attribute (configured in playwright.config.ts)
await page.getByTestId('submit-button').click();
await page.getByTestId('user-profile-card');
```

✅ Extremely resilient and stable — `data-drid` values are intentionally placed by devs with unique values
✅ Immune to text/label changes
ℹ️ Custom attribute in this project: `data-drid`

[Playwright Locator Hierarchy > Priority Order > 2. `getByLabel()`]

**For form controls with labels**

```typescript
await page.getByLabel('Username').fill('john');
await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('secret');
```

[Playwright Locator Hierarchy > Advanced Patterns > Handling Multiple Elements]

```typescript
// First element
await page.getByRole('button').first().click();

// Nth element (0-indexed)
await page.getByRole('button').nth(2).click();

// Last element
await page.getByRole('button').last().click();
```

