[Assertion Best Practices > Auto-Retrying vs. Non-Retrying > Auto-Retrying Assertions (for UI elements)]

Use for UI state - automatically retries until timeout:

```typescript
// ✅ Use for UI state - automatically retries until timeout
await expect(locator).toBeVisible();
await expect(locator).toHaveText('expected text');
await expect(locator).toBeEnabled();
await expect(page).toHaveURL('https://example.com');
await expect(locator).toHaveCount(5);

// With custom timeout
await expect(locator).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15000 });
```

**When to use:**

- Checking element visibility
- Verifying text content
- Checking element state (enabled/disabled)
- URL verification
- Element count with polling

[Assertion Best Practices > Auto-Retrying vs. Non-Retrying > Non-Retrying Assertions (for data)]

Use for pure data checks - evaluates once:

```typescript
// ✅ Use for pure data checks - evaluates once
expect(value).toBe(expectedValue);
expect(array).toContain(item);
expect(object).toHaveProperty('propertyName');
```

**When to use:**

- Comparing values
- Array/object checks
- Mathematical assertions
- Boolean checks

