[Common Examples of Flaky Tests and How to Fix Them > Example 1: Checking Element Visibility]

Flaky (non-retrying on UI state):
```ts
test('submit form and check confirmation', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/form');
  await page.locator('input#name').fill('John Doe');
  await page.locator('input#email').fill('john@example.com');
  await page.locator('button[type="submit"]').click();

  // ❌ FLAKY
  const confirmationMessage = page.locator('.confirmation-message');
  expect(await confirmationMessage.isVisible()).toBe(true);
});
```

Fixed (auto-retrying):
```ts
test('submit form and check confirmation', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/form');
  await page.locator('input#name').fill('John Doe');
  await page.locator('input#email').fill('john@example.com');
  await page.locator('button[type="submit"]').click();

  // ✅ STABLE
  const confirmationMessage = page.locator('.confirmation-message');
  await expect(confirmationMessage).toBeVisible();

  await expect(page.locator('.delayed-notification')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10000 });
});
```

