[Tier 1: Co-First Priority — `getByRole()` and `getByTestId()` > `page.getByRole()`]

**Best for:** Interactive elements (buttons, links, inputs, headings)

```typescript
// Always include accessible name
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign In' }).click();
await page.getByRole('textbox', { name: 'Email' }).fill('user@example.com');
await page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Welcome' });
```

**Why it's recommended:** Reflects how users and assistive technologies perceive the page. Helps surface accessibility issues early since roles and labels must be properly defined.

[Tier 1: Co-First Priority — `getByRole()` and `getByTestId()` > `page.getByTestId()`]

**Best for:** Elements with `data-drid` attributes, or when user-facing attributes are unreliable

```typescript
// Uses data-drid attribute (configured in playwright.config.ts)
await page.getByTestId('submit-button').click();
await page.getByTestId('user-profile-card');
```

**Why it's co-first in this project:** `data-drid` values are intentionally placed by developers with unique, descriptive values. They are immune to text/label changes and extremely resilient across environments.

**Configuration:**
```typescript
// playwright.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  use: {
    testIdAttribute: 'data-drid',
  },
});
```

