[Anti-Patterns to Avoid > ❌ Fixed Time Delays]

```typescript
// Bad - Unreliable and slow
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);
await page.click('button');

// Good - Auto-waiting
await page.getByRole('button').click();
```

[Anti-Patterns to Avoid > ❌ Brittle Selectors]

```typescript
// Bad - Tied to implementation
await page.locator('.header > .nav > .menu > .item:nth-child(3)').click();

// Good - User-facing
await page.getByRole('link', { name: 'Products' }).click();
```

[Anti-Patterns to Avoid > ❌ Improper Assertions]

```typescript
// Bad - No retry, flaky
expect(await page.locator('button').isVisible()).toBe(true);

// Good - Auto-retrying
await expect(page.locator('button')).toBeVisible();
```

[Anti-Patterns to Avoid > ❌ Using `locator.all()` on Dynamic Content]

```typescript
// Bad - Bypasses auto-waiting, resolves immediately
const items = await page.getByRole('listitem').all();
// Items might be stale or incomplete if list is still loading

// Good - Wait for stability first, then use all()
await expect(page.getByRole('listitem')).toHaveCount(5);
const items = await page.getByRole('listitem').all();
```

